{{Unreferenced|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Specific kinetic energy''' is [[kinetic energy]] of an object per unit of mass.

It is defined as <math> \begin{matrix} e_k = \frac{1}{2} \end{matrix} v^2 </math>.

Where <math>e_k</math> is the specific kinetic energy and <math>v</math> is velocity. It has units of J/kg, which is equivalent to m<sup>2</sup>/s<sup>2</sup>.

